==English==
===Alternative spellings===
* [[brahmadaṇḍa]] ''(with diacritics)''

===Etymology===
Sanskrit [[ब्रह्मन्]] ''(Brahman,'' [[Brahma]]) + [[दण्ड]] ''(daṇḍa,'' [[rod]], [[staff]]).

===Noun===
'''brahmadanda'''

# Literally, the rod of Brahma; also used of bamboo rods carried by Indian ascetics.
# A form of punishment, apparently social excommunication.
# ''(Indian mysticism)'' The [[spine]].

===Quotations===
* '''1915,''' ''The Yoga of Yama'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=Y3pu3dPCkl0C&pg=PA29&lpg=PA29&sig=z_3oKOSovds7ZWMP5zmgi4rOV5g]
*: This fennel-stalk is equivalent to the '''Brahmadanda,''' the bamboo rod of seven knots used by the Yogis and Sadhus. Physiologically it corresponds with the spinal column and the spinal ganglia, [...]
* '''1975,''' Charles S. Prebish, “Buddhist Councils and Divisions in the Order,” in ''Buddhism—A Modern Perspective,'' Charles S Prebish, ed. [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=u_AEQHfY_OoC&pg=PA22&lpg=PA22&sig=el_TvaGpTP67GsSR5oAQWQVN-gc]
*: Ānanda relates that Buddha declared that after his death, the '''''Brahmadaṇḍa''''' penalty (i.e., social excommunication) was to be imposed on ''Channa,'' his childhood charioteer for renouncing the world like his master.
* '''1993,''' Yves Bonnefoy, ''Asian Mythologies'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=r4I-FsZCzJEC&pg=PA54&lpg=PA54&sig=RpmdK-X46ebpXiKUTFMQ8PgJ8G0]
*: All Vasiṣṭha has to do is counter with his Brahman’s stick—the '''''brahmadaṇḍa'''''—to annul the effect of Viśvāmitra’s weapons.
* '''(2005)''' [[w:Helena Petrovna Blavatsky|Helena Petrovna Blavatsky]], ''The Esoteric Papers of Madame Blavatsky'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=a0mOFWsuMp4C&pg=PA611&lpg=PA611&sig=LQsJjSyAaWvYvuiRd_gJSxUU-Ag]
*: The Spinal Column is called '''Brahmadanda''', the rod or stick of Brahma, and it is this which is symbolized by the bamboo rod carried by ascetics, the seven-knotted wand of the Yogi.